\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid155753 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11212422\charrsid11812698 Can you tell me something of how you spent Saturdays in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8026712 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11212422\charrsid11812698 Well as - small boys we used to l
ike to play pretty well about - play with friends in the street, or, in the early days, in the field that was all round here which is now built on of course. That was a field, an open field - so we had plenty of room to play. We'd probably have a few erra
n
ds to do - if we could be dragged away from play. Aye, perhaps so, or mother would probably tell us - I want you to do me a few errands before you go playing. You see, give us warning. Could be those few errands, local errands to do. Afternoon was rather 
a
 - the less organized sort of period, and I don't think - we ever did anything very special there. Evenings as I say we - we should just be - about here. We - we might go out - some of us might go out with mother - on her shopping expeditions to market - 
in the evening, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid155753 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11212422\charrsid11812698 What about Sundays, did you have different clothes to wear on Sundays?
