\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid155753 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11212422\charrsid11812698 That were kept specially for Sundays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8026712 GC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11212422\charrsid11812698 Yes. Yes. Sailor suits when we were very small. 'Cos they were v
ery popular in those days were sailor suits with - what they called turkey red - collars. Oh at Monday morning we'd - Sunday morning we'd just - might say - play about a little, but never - never off the premises, we'd never go into the street or - see - 
any of the other boys. 'Cos you'd never dream of that at all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid155753 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11212422\charrsid11812698 Did your parents think it wrong to play or to work on Sunday?
