No, it's nothing to do with Methodist, no. No, no. They used to be in - a century ago - a very small clique of people in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}Lancashire{\*\xmlclose}
 who got the name of - Methodist Unitarians but - it - it was only temporary. No, we - we're not connected with the Methodis
ts - because after all they are - they're orthodox, they accept the orthodox-normally they accept the orthodox - beliefs of a - of a - the virgin birth and such like, the emaculate conception and - they believe in miracles and - the belief that Jesus was 
- was actually God and so forth, which of course we don't believe, we accept that }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5711905\charrsid11812698 Jesus}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
