 have the Sunday school outings - in the summer. Sometimes it was case of - a field somewhere just outside the town. The usual races you know and - small prizes. I remember one occasion we - we went in the old fashioned brakes, horsedrawn brakes, you've p
robably never seen any. Horsedrawn brakes. Two - to Congleton. Remember that very plainly.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid155753 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11212422\charrsid11812698 What did you find to do at Congleton?
